= KISS Generator

Keep it stupid simple (or simple stupid) code generator. 

== Installation

  gem install kissgen

== API Usage

  require 'rcgen'
  @g = KISSGen::Generator.new "/path/to/generator", "/path/where/files/are/generated"
  @g.directory = "/"
  @g.assign :my_name, "lancelot"
  @g.generate(:pretend => true)
  @g.generate
  
Instead of using @g.directory and @g.assign, you can also create a setup.rb file inside of your generator directory
and run the instance methods directly from there. IE:
  
setup.rb:

  directory "/app"
  file "README"
  
== Console Usage

  kissgen /path/to/generator /path/where/files/are/generated

== Repository

  visit http://github.com/lancecarlson/kissgen/ or git clone git://github.com/lancecarlson/kissgen.git